# Consumer Contracts

This directory documents target-side values that should be injected by the consuming playbook or machine-local setup.

Preferred patterns:

- interactive shell values: drop `*.zsh` snippets into `~/.local/config/shell/`
- script-specific non-interactive values: write role-specific env files in `{{ consumer_contract_env_dir }}`
- app-native secrets/config: render the real config file directly from the consuming playbook
- personal secrets: prefer `rbw` or `pass` when the tool can fetch at runtime
- services: only use systemd user environment when the application truly needs it

This public repo intentionally does not manage private values directly.
